---
// Figure: Alternative access is a separate threat model
// Three columns — primary digital, alternative digitised, human casework.
// Five rows — disclosure boundary, fraud surface, verification method,
// revocation handling, support model.
// Point: each route is its own design problem, not a fallback.
---

<div class="reveal my-12 md:my-16">
  <div class="rounded-2xl border border-border overflow-hidden" style="background: rgba(11,11,17,0.6);">
    <div class="p-6 md:p-8">

      <div class="mb-6">
        <p class="text-text-tertiary text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.2em] uppercase mb-1">Access design</p>
        <h3 class="text-text-primary font-display font-bold text-lg tracking-tight">Alternative access is a separate threat model</h3>
      </div>

      <!-- Route headers -->
      <div class="grid grid-cols-[10rem,1fr,1fr,1fr] gap-3 mb-3 pb-3 border-b border-border/50">
        <div></div>
        <div class="text-center">
          <p class="text-[10px] font-mono tracking-[0.15em] uppercase text-text-tertiary mb-1">Route 01</p>
          <p class="text-xs font-display font-semibold text-text-primary">Primary digital</p>
        </div>
        <div class="text-center">
          <p class="text-[10px] font-mono tracking-[0.15em] uppercase text-text-tertiary mb-1">Route 02</p>
          <p class="text-xs font-display font-semibold text-text-primary">Alternative digitised</p>
        </div>
        <div class="text-center">
          <p class="text-[10px] font-mono tracking-[0.15em] uppercase text-text-tertiary mb-1">Route 03</p>
          <p class="text-xs font-display font-semibold text-text-primary">Human support · casework</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Dimension rows -->
      <div class="divide-y divide-border/40 text-sm">

        <!-- Row: Disclosure boundary -->
        <div class="grid grid-cols-[10rem,1fr,1fr,1fr] gap-3 py-3 md:py-4">
          <div class="text-[11px] font-semibold tracking-[0.12em] uppercase text-text-tertiary pt-1">Disclosure boundary</div>
          <div class="text-text-secondary text-xs md:text-sm leading-snug">Selective claim disclosure, enforced by the wallet and checker protocol.</div>
          <div class="text-text-secondary text-xs md:text-sm leading-snug">Signed code or QR, scoped to a single check, carrying only the claims required.</div>
          <div class="text-text-secondary text-xs md:text-sm leading-snug">Bounded by a defined evidence list and a case officer’s logged purpose.</div>
        </div>

        <!-- Row: Fraud surface -->
        <div class="grid grid-cols-[10rem,1fr,1fr,1fr] gap-3 py-3 md:py-4">
          <div class="text-[11px] font-semibold tracking-[0.12em] uppercase text-text-tertiary pt-1">Fraud surface</div>
          <div class="text-text-secondary text-xs md:text-sm leading-snug">Device compromise, phishing of the wallet flow, relying-party impersonation.</div>
          <div class="text-text-secondary text-xs md:text-sm leading-snug">Replay of codes or QR artefacts, screenshotting, social engineering at the counter.</div>
          <div class="text-text-secondary text-xs md:text-sm leading-snug">Impersonation in person, forged supporting evidence, casework capture by bad actors.</div>
        </div>

        <!-- Row: Verification method -->
        <div class="grid grid-cols-[10rem,1fr,1fr,1fr] gap-3 py-3 md:py-4">
          <div class="text-[11px] font-semibold tracking-[0.12em] uppercase text-text-tertiary pt-1">Verification method</div>
          <div class="text-text-secondary text-xs md:text-sm leading-snug">Cryptographic check against issuer status and a live checker endpoint.</div>
          <div class="text-text-secondary text-xs md:text-sm leading-snug">Digitised check against the same issuer status, via the alternative artefact.</div>
          <div class="text-text-secondary text-xs md:text-sm leading-snug">Protocolised officer check against documented evidence, not visual guesswork.</div>
        </div>

        <!-- Row: Revocation handling -->
        <div class="grid grid-cols-[10rem,1fr,1fr,1fr] gap-3 py-3 md:py-4">
          <div class="text-[11px] font-semibold tracking-[0.12em] uppercase text-text-tertiary pt-1">Revocation handling</div>
          <div class="text-text-secondary text-xs md:text-sm leading-snug">Status check refreshes on every verification. Revoked credentials fail closed.</div>
          <div class="text-text-secondary text-xs md:text-sm leading-snug">Artefact bound to credential status; revocation invalidates future presentations.</div>
          <div class="text-text-secondary text-xs md:text-sm leading-snug">Case record reflects current status; officers cannot override a revoked credential.</div>
        </div>

        <!-- Row: Support model -->
        <div class="grid grid-cols-[10rem,1fr,1fr,1fr] gap-3 py-3 md:py-4">
          <div class="text-[11px] font-semibold tracking-[0.12em] uppercase text-text-tertiary pt-1">Support model</div>
          <div class="text-text-secondary text-xs md:text-sm leading-snug">Self service with helpline escalation; failure modes documented.</div>
          <div class="text-text-secondary text-xs md:text-sm leading-snug">Face to face help during rollout and afterwards; accessible at point of use.</div>
          <div class="text-text-secondary text-xs md:text-sm leading-snug">Dedicated casework for coercive control, no fixed address, disability, digital exclusion.</div>
        </div>

      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
  <p class="text-text-tertiary text-xs mt-3 text-center italic">
    Alternative access is not a degraded fallback. Each route carries its own disclosure rules, fraud surface, revocation semantics, and support model — and must be designed with those users in the room.
  </p>
</div>
